FBIS4-55715 "dreeu098_b_94002" FBIS-EEU-94-098 Daily Report 20 May 1994 BULGARIA Assembly Votes Against Structural Changes Assembly Votes Against Structural Changes AU2005103794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1014 GMT 20 May 94 AU2005103794 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Bulgarian BFN [Report by unidentified correspondent on National Assembly debate on cabinet changes proposed by Prime Minister Lyuben Berov at the National Assembly in Sofia -- live] [Text] Today's session of the National Assembly has just ended. After the National Assembly rejected the structural changes to the cabinet proposed by Prime Minister Lyuben Berov, the prime minister declared that he will have to ask for a vote of confidence in his cabinet. Under the Constitution, the Cabinet has to submit a proposal in writing for such a vote.
